cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the coordinated movement of a network of vehicles, which involves control and communication aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and design of complex systems. The paper also involves multi-agent systems, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The use of graph theory and network analysis in the paper suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics), which deals with the design and control of robots and autonomous systems. The paper also involves communication and networking aspects, which could place it under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with the resilience of the network against malicious agents, which could place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which deals with the design and analysis of distributed systems.
